{"title_page": "Periya Gounder Ponnu", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2016}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=October 2016}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Periya Gounder Ponnu\n| image          = \n| image_size     =\n| caption        = \n| director       = [[Manivasagam]]\n| producer       = Rajeswari Manivasagam<br />P. S. Mani\n| writer         = Manivasagam<br />Erode Soundar <small>(dialogues)</small>\n| starring       = {{ubl|[[R. Sarathkumar]]|[[Gautami]]|[[Manorama (Tamil actress)|Manorama]]|[[Goundamani]]|[[Senthil]]|[[Jai Ganesh]]|[[Vadivukkarasi]]|[[Delhi Ganesh]]|Vijayaraj}}\n| music          = [[Deva (composer)|Deva]]\n| cinematography = R. H. Ashok\n| editing        = L. Kesavan\n| distributor    =\n| studio         = Raaja Pushpa Pictures\n| released       = {{Film date|df=y|1992|02|28}}\n| runtime        = 145 minutes\n| country        = India\n| language       = Tamil\n}}\n\n'''''Periya Gounder Ponnu''''' ({{Translation}} Daughter of a big landlord) is a 1992 [[India]]n [[Tamil language|Tamil]]-language [[drama film]], directed by [[Manivasagam]]. The film features [[R. Sarathkumar]] and [[Gautami]], with [[Manorama (Tamil actress)|Manorama]], [[Goundamani]], [[Senthil]], [[Jaiganesh]], [[Vadivukkarasi]], [[Delhi Ganesh]] and Vijayaraj in supporting roles. The film, produced by Rajeswari Manivasagam and P. S. Mani, had musical score by [[Deva (composer)|Deva]] and was released on 28 February 1992.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://spicyonion.com/movie/periya-kaundar-ponnu/|title=Periya Kaunder Ponnu (1992) Tamil Movie|accessdate=2016-10-03|publisher=spicyonion.com}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\n\nPeriya Samy ([[Jai Ganesh]]), called Periya Gounder by the villagers, is the village chief and a wealthy respected man in his village. His daughter Manjula ([[Gautami]]), an arrogant girl who studied in the city, comes back to her village during summer vacations. Her cousin Thangamuthu ([[R. Sarathkumar]]) is an educated blacksmith and lives with his widow mother ([[Manorama (Tamil actress)|Manorama]]), he is the future husband of Manjula as per the village custom. But Periya Samy doesn't want to marry a man from a poor family, so he refuses Thangamuthu and Manjula's marriage.\n\nPeriya Samy slowly falls in love with the village belle Jillu (Jillu) and she becomes his secret mistress. He even accepts to marry his daughter with his mistress's rowdy brother (Vijayaraj). One day, Manjula insults Thangamuthu and his mother. Then, angry, he ties a mangalsutra around her neck (synonym of marriage). What transpires next forms the rest of the story.\n\n==Cast==\n\n{{colbegin}}\n*[[R. Sarathkumar]] as Thangamuthu\n*[[Gautami]] as Manjula\n*[[Manorama (Tamil actress)|Manorama]] as Thangamuthu's mother\n*[[Goundamani]] as Pazhanisamy\n*[[Senthil]]\n*[[Jai Ganesh]] as Periya Samy (Periya Gounder)\n*[[Vadivukkarasi]] as Deivatha\n*[[Delhi Ganesh]] as Thangamuthu's father\n*Vijayaraj\n*[[Pasi Narayanan]]\n*Jillu as Jillu\n*[[Thideer Kannaiah]]\n*Sharmili as Kanthamani\n*Karuppu Subbiah\n*Senji Krishnan\n*Chandrika\n*Umasri\n{{colend}}\n\n==Soundtrack==\n\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Periya Gounder Ponnu\n| type       = [[soundtrack]]\n| artist     = [[Deva (composer)|Deva]]\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = 1992\n| recorded   = 1992\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Film soundtrack|Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length     = 22:10\n| label      =\n| producer   = [[Deva (composer)|Deva]]\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n}}\n\nThe film score and the soundtrack were composed by [[film composer]] [[Deva (composer)|Deva]]. The soundtrack, released in 1992, features 5 tracks with lyrics written by Kalidasan.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mio.to/album/Periya+Goundar+Ponnu+%281995%29|title=Periya+Goundar+Ponnu+(1992)|accessdate=2016-10-03|publisher=mio.to}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.saavn.com/s/album/tamil/Periya-Goundar-Ponnu-1992/hvtGo4Y12BY_|title=Periya Goundar Ponnu songs|accessdate=2016-10-03|publisher=saavn.com}}</ref>\n\n{| border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%;\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#CCCCCC\" align=\"center\"\n! Track !! Song !! Singer(s) !! Duration\n|-\n|1 || \"Summa Summa\" || [[Mano (singer)|Mano]] || 4:16\n|-\n|2 || \"Kottampatti\" || [[Malaysia Vasudevan]], [[Swarnalatha]] || 4:39\n|-\n|3 || \"Chikku Mukku\" || [[S. Janaki]] || 4:23\n|-\n|4 || \"Nalu Vartha\" || Krishnaraj || 4:42\n|-\n|5 || \"Umai Kuyil Onnu\" || Malaysia Vasudevan, Sundar || 4:10\n|}\n\n==Reception==\n''The Indian Express'' wrote \"Such a skewed scenario notwithstanding, director Manivasagam keeps the drama going because og good performanes [..].\"<ref>https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=P9oYG7HA76QC&dat=19920403&printsec=frontpage&hl=en</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:1992 films]]\n[[Category:1990s Tamil-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:Indian drama films]]\n[[Category:Tamil-language films]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Deva (composer)]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2016}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=October 2016}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Periya Gounder Ponnu\n| image          = \n| image_size     =\n| caption        = \n| director       = [[Manivasagam]]\n| producer       = Rajeswari Manivasagam<br />P. S. Mani\n| writer         = Manivasagam<br />Erode Soundar <small>(dialogues)</small>\n| starring       = {{ubl|[[R. Sarathkumar]]|[[Gautami]]|[[Manorama (Tamil actress)|Manorama]]|[[Goundamani]]|[[Senthil]]|[[Jai Ganesh]]|[[Vadivukkarasi]]|[[Delhi Ganesh]]|Vijayaraj}}\n| music          = [[Deva (composer)|Deva]]\n| cinematography = R. H. Ashok\n| editing        = L. Kesavan\n| distributor    =\n| studio         = Raaja Pushpa Pictures\n| released       = {{Film date|df=y|1992|02|28}}\n| runtime        = 145 minutes\n| country        = India\n| language       = Tamil\n}}\n\n'''''Periya Gounder Ponnu''''' ({{Translation}} Daughter of a big landlord) is a 1992 [[India]]n [[Tamil language|Tamil]]-language [[drama film]], directed by [[Manivasagam]]. The film features [[R. Sarathkumar]] and [[Gautami]], with [[Manorama (Tamil actress)|Manorama]], [[Goundamani]], [[Senthil]], [[Jaiganesh]], [[Vadivukkarasi]], [[Delhi Ganesh]] and Vijayaraj in supporting roles. The film, produced by Rajeswari Manivasagam and P. S. Mani, had musical score by [[Deva (composer)|Deva]] and was released on 28 February 1992.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://spicyonion.com/movie/periya-kaundar-ponnu/|title=Periya Kaunder Ponnu (1992) Tamil Movie|accessdate=2016-10-03|publisher=spicyonion.com}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\n\nPeriya Samy ([[Jai Ganesh]]), called Periya Gounder by the villagers, is the village chief and a wealthy respected man in his village. His daughter Manjula ([[Gautami]]), an arrogant girl who studied in the city, comes back to her village during summer vacations. Her cousin Thangamuthu ([[R. Sarathkumar]]) is an educated blacksmith and lives with his widow mother ([[Manorama (Tamil actress)|Manorama]]), he is the future husband of Manjula as per the village custom. But Periya Samy doesn't want to get married to a man who belongs to a poor family, so he refuses Thangamuthu and Manjula's marriage.\n\nPeriya Samy slowly falls in love with the village belle Jillu (Jillu) and she becomes his secret mistress. He even accepts to marry his daughter with his mistress's rowdy brother (Vijayaraj). One day, Manjula insults Thangamuthu and his mother. Then, angry, he ties a mangalsutra around her neck (synonym of marriage). What transpires next forms the rest of the story.\n\n==Cast==\n\n{{colbegin}}\n*[[R. Sarathkumar]] as Thangamuthu\n*[[Gautami]] as Manjula\n*[[Manorama (Tamil actress)|Manorama]] as Thangamuthu's mother\n*[[Goundamani]] as Pazhanisamy\n*[[Senthil]]\n*[[Jai Ganesh]] as Periya Samy (Periya Gounder)\n*[[Vadivukkarasi]] as Deivatha\n*[[Delhi Ganesh]] as Thangamuthu's father\n*Vijayaraj\n*[[Pasi Narayanan]]\n*Jillu as Jillu\n*[[Thideer Kannaiah]]\n*Sharmili as Kanthamani\n*Karuppu Subbiah\n*Senji Krishnan\n*Chandrika\n*Umasri\n{{colend}}\n\n==Soundtrack==\n\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Periya Gounder Ponnu\n| type       = [[soundtrack]]\n| artist     = [[Deva (composer)|Deva]]\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = 1992\n| recorded   = 1992\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Film soundtrack|Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length     = 22:10\n| label      =\n| producer   = [[Deva (composer)|Deva]]\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n}}\n\nThe film score and the soundtrack were composed by [[film composer]] [[Deva (composer)|Deva]]. The soundtrack, released in 1992, features 5 tracks with lyrics written by Kalidasan.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mio.to/album/Periya+Goundar+Ponnu+%281995%29|title=Periya+Goundar+Ponnu+(1992)|accessdate=2016-10-03|publisher=mio.to}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.saavn.com/s/album/tamil/Periya-Goundar-Ponnu-1992/hvtGo4Y12BY_|title=Periya Goundar Ponnu songs|accessdate=2016-10-03|publisher=saavn.com}}</ref>\n\n{| border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%;\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#CCCCCC\" align=\"center\"\n! Track !! Song !! Singer(s) !! Duration\n|-\n|1 || \"Summa Summa\" || [[Mano (singer)|Mano]] || 4:16\n|-\n|2 || \"Kottampatti\" || [[Malaysia Vasudevan]], [[Swarnalatha]] || 4:39\n|-\n|3 || \"Chikku Mukku\" || [[S. Janaki]] || 4:23\n|-\n|4 || \"Nalu Vartha\" || Krishnaraj || 4:42\n|-\n|5 || \"Umai Kuyil Onnu\" || Malaysia Vasudevan, Sundar || 4:10\n|}\n\n==Reception==\n''The Indian Express'' wrote \"Such a skewed scenario notwithstanding, director Manivasagam keeps the drama going because og good performanes [..].\"<ref>https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=P9oYG7HA76QC&dat=19920403&printsec=frontpage&hl=en<